{"id": 7067, "title": "Ticket #7067: Construct Submit object from arbitrary keyword arguments", "description": "<blockquote>\nInstead of forcing users to generate a dictionary and passing that to <code>Submit</code>, we should allow them to provide arbitrary key-value pairs.\n\n<p></p><div class=\"code\">\n<pre class=\"code\">&gt;&gt;&gt; import htcondor\n&gt;&gt;&gt; htcondor.Submit(executable = \"/bin/sleep\", arguments=\"5m\")\n'executable = /bin/sleep\\narguments = 5m\\n'\n</pre></div>\n</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-May-22 17:07:09 by karpel:</em> <br/>\n\nIdeally the constructor API should be the same as <code>dict</code>: <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#dict\">https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#dict</a>, PLUS the ability to accept a single string as a slurped-up submit file.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Aug-02 09:47</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/0f661891027ae0786a4cf4afe045a7cecc1073a0\">[57556]</a></span>: Add release notes for Submit constructor changes. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7067\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7067'); return false;\" title=\"Construct Submit object from arbitrary keyword arguments\">#7067</a></span>  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-May-23 08:46</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/2d852c8bdb5938feb61f393d08b2d50e650b1947\">[56946]</a></span>: Use dict-like constructor. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7067\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7067'); return false;\" title=\"Construct Submit object from arbitrary keyword arguments\">#7067</a></span>  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-May-22 16:02</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/c8f08bc1b7c47531161626b5a1488988a7bc7a6d\">[56945]</a></span>: Allow submit objects to be constructed from keyword args. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7067\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7067'); return false;\" title=\"Construct Submit object from arbitrary keyword arguments\">#7067</a></span>  (By Brian Bockelman )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2019-Aug-02 09:48", "status": "resolved", "created": "2019-May-22 15:58", "fixed_version": "2019-May-22 15:58", "broken_version": "", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "PythonBinding", "assigned_to": "bbockelm", "derived_from": "#7063", "creator": "bbockelm", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "karpel@wisc.edu", "due_date": ""}